Before use:
=============================

1. git clone git://github.com/joyent/node.git
2. cd node
3. git checkout v0.6.15
4. sudo ./configure
5. sudo make
6. sudo make install
7. install mongodb (link http://docs.mongodb.org/master/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-debian-or-ubuntu-linux/)

After install envirotments:
=============================

1. git clone git://github.com/isqad88/nodejs-sample-blog.git
2. cd nodejs-sample-blog
3. npm install -d
4. node app.js